HEADWORD: Xanthophyll
<hw>Xan"tho*phyll</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xantho-</ets> + Gr. <grk>fy`llon</grk> leaf.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A yellow coloring matter found in yellow autumn
leaves, and also produced artificially from chlorophyll; -- formerly
called also <altname>phylloxanthin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xanthopous</ent>⟦br⟧
